issue.title: Support markdown display in reply
issue.body:
### Which application is this bug report for?

Guide

### Issue description

> Well its more an ui package request, idk why i havent posted the issue with that form

Message replies arent displaying markdown

![image](https://github.com/discordjs/discord.js/assets/76836550/57c26b8f-4def-4de7-8cf1-5a31ccd1794c)


### Steps to Reproduce

Just look at reply example

### Versions

Not applicable

### Issue priority

Low (slightly annoying)

comment.body: I've investigated this issue and it seems like the problem lies with [upstream mdx not supporting markdown within parameters](https://github.com/mdx-js/mdx/issues/628#issuecomment-678662324). The `DiscordMessageReply` UI component currently [takes in the reply content](https://github.com/discordjs/discord.js/blob/e80194e3fb186269e479f0a5a323580103e584c0/packages/ui/src/lib/components/discord/Message.tsx#L34) through `DiscordMessage`'s [`reply.content` prop](https://github.com/discordjs/discord.js/blob/e80194e3fb186269e479f0a5a323580103e584c0/packages/ui/src/lib/components/discord/MessageReply.tsx#L8), meaning mdx will not render markdown within that `reply.content` string.

issue.title: Localizations responds with Unhandled Rejection
issue.body:
### Which package is this bug report for?

discord.js

### Issue description

1. Create a slash command builder and add localizations with .setDescription/NameLocalizations
2. Run the bot
3. Gives unhandled rejection when trying to register commands
4. Unhandled Rejection at: Promise {
  <rejected> ExpectedConstraintError > s.string.regex
    Invalid string format

    Expected: expected /^[\p{Ll}\p{Lm}\p{Lo}\p{N}\p{sc=Devanagari}\p{sc=Thai}_-]+$/u.test(expected) to be true

    Received:
    | 'Версия'

      at Object.run (E:\TeamBG4.0\node_modules\@sapphire\shapeshift\dist\index.js:1592:64)
      at E:\TeamBG4.0\node_modules\@sapphire\shapeshift\dist\index.js:212:66
      at Array.reduce (<anonymous>)
      at StringValidator.parse (E:\TeamBG4.0\node_modules\@sapphire\shapeshift\dist\index.js:212:29)
      at validateName (E:\TeamBG4.0\node_modules\@discordjs\builders\dist\index.js:1428:17)
      at MixedClass.setNameLocalization (E:\TeamBG4.0\node_modules\@discordjs\builders\dist\index.js:1557:5)
      at MixedClass.setNameLocalizations (E:\TeamBG4.0\node_modules\@discordjs\builders\dist\index.js:1573:12)
      at Object.<anonymous> (E:\TeamBG4.0\src\commands\Community\version.js:6:8)
      at Module._compile (node:internal/modules/cjs/loader:1241:14)
      at Module._extensions..js (node:internal/modules/cjs/loader:1295:10)
} reason: ExpectedConstraintError > s.string.regex
  Invalid string format

  Expected: expected /^[\p{Ll}\p{Lm}\p{Lo}\p{N}\p{sc=Devanagari}\p{sc=Thai}_-]+$/u.test(expected) to be true

  Received:
  | 'Версия'

    at Object.run (E:\TeamBG4.0\node_modules\@sapphire\shapeshift\dist\index.js:1592:64)
    at E:\TeamBG4.0\node_modules\@sapphire\shapeshift\dist\index.js:212:66
    at Array.reduce (<anonymous>)
    at StringValidator.parse (E:\TeamBG4.0\node_modules\@sapphire\shapeshift\dist\index.js:212:29)
    at validateName (E:\TeamBG4.0\node_modules\@discordjs\builders\dist\index.js:1428:17)
    at MixedClass.setNameLocalization (E:\TeamBG4.0\node_modules\@discordjs\builders\dist\index.js:1557:5)
    at MixedClass.setNameLocalizations (E:\TeamBG4.0\node_modules\@discordjs\builders\dist\index.js:1573:12)
    at Object.<anonymous> (E:\TeamBG4.0\src\commands\Community\version.js:6:8)
    at Module._compile (node:internal/modules/cjs/loader:1241:14)
    at Module._extensions..js (node:internal/modules/cjs/loader:1295:10)

### Code sample

```typescript
const { SlashCommandBuilder, EmbedBuilder} = require('discord.js');

module.exports = {
    data: new SlashCommandBuilder()
      .setName(`version`)
      .setNameLocalizations({ ru: 'Версия' })
      .setDescription(`Gives the version of the bot`)
      .setDescriptionLocalizations({ ru: 'Выдает версию бота' }),
```


### Versions

discord.js@14.12.1
node.js v20.9.0
Microsoft Windows [Version 10.0.19045.3570]

### Issue priority

Medium (should be fixed soon)

### Which partials do you have configured?

No Partials

### Which gateway intents are you subscribing to?

Guilds, GuildMembers
